+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"},{"content_hash":"67f4732c5a008660cb323b4612a9f8af5bdb3f5e0c2d734e96d20898169c9e71","event_uuid":"2e35d6fe-5aea-47b4-b916-dd18656ec9fb","position":{"commit_sha":"8d3f3d861224fce3d0c10b4978b32051a25fb137","position":"1784352205956622167-2e35d6fe-5aea-47b4-b916-dd18656ec9fb"},"signature":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","signer_pubkey":"ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3NzaC1lZDI1NTE5AAAAIHe3p+OG3L79IIh99qRBEkAEXaU+VbeQcSfhIu4M2F8b rebar-bot joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com"}],"bridge_alerts":[],"claim_harness":"claude-code_2-1-214_agent","claim_remote_session":null,"claimed_session":"671b0000-304e-44ce-9bea-3e57bbd2e0fb","comments":[{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","body":"Pushed CodeQL docs/** exclusion to Gerrit change 784 (https://rebar.solutions.navateam.com/c/rebar/+/784). Two files: new .github/codeql/codeql-config.yml (paths-ignore: docs/**) + wiring in .github/workflows/codeql.yml init. Awaiting LLM-Review + Verified gates before submit. All 4 AC verified locally in worktree.","timestamp":1784350558318269001}],"created_at":1784349980302357001,"creation_channel":"cli","deps":[{"link_uuid":"1f176380-694e-4ab2-b78b-1a4c97e464b6","relation":"relates_to","target_id":"488a-24f2-4058-46c2"}],"description":"## Why\nThe GitHub CodeQL \"Security and quality\" scan flags `py/clear-text-logging-sensitive-data` in\n`docs/experiments/workflow-remediation-pocs/runtime_pydanticai_poc.py` (code-scanning alerts 3 and 4).\nThat file is a hand-run proof-of-concept: it is not packaged (the wheel/sdist ship only `src/rebar` —\n`pyproject.toml:213`), is on no `import rebar` path, and never runs in production. The findings are\nfalse positives (they log public provider-name strings such as \"anthropic\"/\"openai\", not secrets). The\nindividual alerts have been dismissed, but any code under `docs/` keeps generating recurring scan noise\non every push. The advanced-setup CodeQL workflow (`.github/workflows/codeql.yml`) currently passes no\nconfig, so nothing is excluded.\n\n## What\nAdd a CodeQL config file that excludes `docs/**` from analysis and wire it into the workflow, so the\nexclusion is durable (survives future `docs/experiments` additions) rather than relying on per-alert\ndismissals.\n- New file `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` with `paths-ignore: [\"docs/**\"]`.\n- Edit `.github/workflows/codeql.yml`: pass `config-file: ./.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` to the\n  `github/codeql-action/init` step. No change to the default query suite (only path scoping).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` exists and its `paths-ignore` list covers `docs/**`.\n- [ ] The CodeQL workflow `init` step (`.github/workflows/codeql.yml`) references that config via `config-file:`.\n- [ ] `python -c \"import yaml,sys; d=yaml.safe_load(open('.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml')); assert 'docs/**' in d['paths-ignore']\"` exits 0 (config parses and contains the exclusion).\n- [ ] No file under `src/rebar` is modified in this change (config/workflow only, so no runtime behavior change) — verified by `git diff --name-only origin/main` listing only `.github/` paths.\n\n## Verification\n- `python -c \"import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml'))\"` — config is valid YAML.\n- `grep -q 'config-file: ./.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml' .github/workflows/codeql.yml` — wiring present.\n- `git diff --name-only origin/main` — shows only `.github/codeql/codeql-config.yml` and `.github/workflows/codeql.yml`.\n\n## Out of scope\n- The 27 valid `py/path-injection` findings and the `py/stack-trace-exposure` finding (alert 27): those\n  need real code fixes and are tracked separately.","env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","file_impact":[{"path":".github/codeql/codeql-config.yml","reason":"New CodeQL config declaring paths-ignore: docs/**"},{"path":".github/workflows/codeql.yml","reason":"Wire config-file into the codeql-action/init step"}],"keyring":[],"last_status_env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","managed_refs":[["relates_to","488a-24f2-4058-46c2"]],"parent_id":null,"parent_status_uuid":"1e049a09-7d4e-4d6d-86d2-e6408ab0fe7f","preconditions_summary":{"status":"pre-manifest"},"priority":3,"reverts":[],"status":"in_progress","tags":["security","codeql","ci"],"ticket_id":"5b57-96cf-7147-43ea","ticket_type":"task","title":"CodeQL: exclude docs/** from scanning (suppress unshipped-POC false positives)","verify_commands":[]},"source_event_uuids":["d3479e04-64ee-4bda-8c9c-ada49923a0e0","1a1b6090-f8c8-496e-bdf7-cf8603b81eb6","1f176380-694e-4ab2-b78b-1a4c97e464b6","d79915da-c3ab-44d3-ac06-6939ad740fa8","f47bd1c8-55c8-46a0-874e-1b249f5fa7a4","1e049a09-7d4e-4d6d-86d2-e6408ab0fe7f","0c69f459-92d9-4895-af6a-f6228a838dc3","9fe54af1-f39e-4e34-92cd-e52d050f210b","2e35d6fe-5aea-47b4-b916-dd18656ec9fb"]},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"SNAPSHOT","timestamp":1784352205956622168,"uuid":"b0cc575a-3b1a-4aab-b484-6c2fc79ff3b3"}